column5: I read the rules THIS year. Now I know that JR cant win all the time.          BUT,He will TONIGHT
Just a bump to see if anyone else wants in. See the first post in this thread for instructions on how to enter.  Good luck guys and gals. Boogity Boogity Boogity..... Let's go racing boys!!!!
Dan,did you figure out how to get your team picked yet? Joe

Hi Joe. Yes I did figured it out. You'll see a "bench" player under each set of picks. In the first and last group you must pick your driver and a "bench" driver. In the second group you pick your 2 drivers and 2 "bench" drivers. Then you'll be able to submit your picks. Don't ask me what the bench driver is for though. Good luck!!
Made my picks.I dont know what the becnh thing is?  Was at work and the light came on the dual was on.Home and watching now. Nice race by Gordon and a real nice save by the pole sitter Truex.

Hello all...  It's almost that time again. The Daytona 500 is a mere 5 weeks away!!  Once again I've created a group for OFC members only in Yahoo fantasy racing. It's just a fun thing that us fishing/racing fans can enjoy throughout the year. It takes only minutes per week to pick your drivers, so if you're not sure about signing up, don't hesitate to give it a try. If it's not your cup of tea, there's no commitment to participate the entire season.  To sign up, click HERE to get to the main page. If you don't already have one, create an identity. Then click "Join a Group". Select "Join a Private Group". Enter group ID# 3363, and Password "hookontario".  That's it.  Hope to see all of the regulars there and a some new faces as well.  Dan
Count me in. Please and Thanks!
